## Implementation Notes

### Attribute Syntax Variations

Support both styles:
```rust
// Simple (no arguments)
#[init]
fn init() -> (Self, Command<Msg>) { ... }

// With arguments
#[init(command = my_startup_command)]
fn init() -> (Self, Command<Msg>) { ... }

// Update with pattern matching hints
#[update(handles(Msg::Tick, Msg::Key(_)))]
fn update(&mut self, msg: Msg) -> Command<Msg> { ... }
```

### Darling Error Recovery

Use darling's error accumulation for multiple validation errors:
```rust
use darling::Error;

let mut errors = Error::accumulator();
errors.handle(validate_init_signature(&init.sig, &struct_name));
errors.handle(validate_update_signature(&update.sig));
errors.handle(validate_view_signature(&view.sig));
errors.finish()?;
```

